properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, second flight eastbound from Manila to San Francisco, March 3-9, 1936; identified by donor with additional information: "Service was suspended due to mechanical problems of needing more power in the engines. Service was not resumed until February 14, 1936. Did not leave San Francisco until February 23";a. cover: cachet with color illustration of aircraft in flight over route map an two statues with text "Via air mail, P.I.-U.S. flight" with handwritten notation of distance between stops and typewritten "2nd flight"; postmark on front: March 3, 1936, Manila, P.I. with football-shaped “1” cancellation mark over one 1-peso stamp and one brown 50-centavos stamp; no backstamp; addressed to Margaret McGibbon.Note: received on .154 b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners with item .154 a mounted on same sheet.
properties.wof:name: airmail flight cover: Pan American Airways, Eastbound from Manila to San Francisco, March 3-9, 1936
